The "'''same-roof rule'''" was a rule of English law that victims of [[Domestic violence|domestic abuse]] are not entitled to compensation if they lived with the perpetrator prior to 1979.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-44939169|title=Woman wins 'same roof' abuse case|date=2018-07-24|work=BBC News|access-date=2018-07-24|language=en-GB}}</ref> The rule was successfully challenged in the [[Court of Appeal]] in 2018.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/07/24/woman-sexually-abused-aged-4-stepdad-wins-landmark-ruling-roof-victims-7754578/|title=Woman abused at 4 by stepdad wins landmark ruling for 'same-roof' victims|date=2018-07-24|work=Metro|access-date=2018-07-24|language=en-GB}}</ref>
